<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2007-02-12</DATELINE><TITLE>Treatment of hypernatremia in neonatal calves with diarrhea</TITLE><BODY>Five hypernatremic, diarrheic, neonatal calves were treated mainly by the intravenous administration of 5% dextrose alone or with isotonic sodium bicarbonate. All calves recovered without complications. The average reduction rate of serum sodium concentration was about 4 times that recommended and has not been tried successfully before in hypernatremic scouring calves.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>